<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Basic Pet modes: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attack</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Free</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Pet behavior is largely determined by whether a pet is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attacking</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Free</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  If a pet has anyone on their <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> within its <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attack Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and is not <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Held</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, then it will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attack</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, following the nearest <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Path</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to the enemy within range nearest the top of its <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and attack them as soon as the pet is within <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Combat Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, either by direct melee or by casting.  A pet with no one within <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attack Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on their <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or which is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Held</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is said to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Free</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and will follow its <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Movement Mode</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> along the nearest <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Path</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attack Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is the furthest distance at which a pet will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Attack</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> an enemy and start moving towards them.  Enemies outside this range remain on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but are not attacked.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Combat Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is the furthest distance at which a pet can directly attack an enemy.  At the outermost <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Combat Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the pet can only cast.  It must be closer in order to melee.<br>
<br>
The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a ranked list of an NPC's immediate enemies.  An <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> NPC</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, such as a pet, will generally attack whichever enemy within <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Combat Range</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that is highest on its <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate List</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  This is discussed in more detail later.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Movement modes: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Follow, Guard, Sit</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Movement Mode</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> determines where the pet goes if it is not attacking, that is, if it is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Free</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The command <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet follow me</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> puts the pet in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Follow</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mode.  The pet will then follow the nearest <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Path</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Path Point</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> nearest its owner.  The command <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet guard here</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pets the pet in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Guard</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mode, and sets the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Guard Point</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to the current location.  The pet then follows the nearest <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Path</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Path Point</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> nearest the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Guard Point</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Note that this means that the pet does not always return to the same location.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet sit</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> puts the pet in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sit</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mode.  If it is not attacking, it will no move from its current location.<br>
<br>
